            <title><![CDATA[The Internet Reacts To John Cena’s First Heel Promo As He Nearly Makes A Kid Cry]]></title>
            <link>https://kotaku.com/john-cena-heel-wwe-raw-netflix-kid-crying-1851770500</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/the-internet-reacts-to-john-cena%E2%80%99s-first-heel-promo-as-he-nearly-makes-a-kid-cry.1137069/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://kotaku.com/john-cena-heel-wwe-raw-netflix-kid-crying-1851770500<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><p>Santa Claus isn’t real, good guys don’t always finish last, and John Cena is not who you thought he was for over 20 years. On March 1 at WWE’s Elimination Chamber, Cena rocked the wrestling world, and likely showed a generation of pre-teens into the disappointment they can expect in adulthood, by effectively selling his soul to The Rock by brutally turning on Cody Rhodes with the grimmest look he’s ever sported in his entire career. Yes, John Cena is a heel. Today, he made his first public appearance as a bad guy on WWE Raw, to the shock, awe, and disgust of the entire wrestling world. Including one small child nearly brought to tears.</p><div><h4>Suggested Reading</h4></div><div data-video-id="197298" data-monetizable="true" data-position="sidebar" data-video-title="Live Forever in the Universe of 'New World: Aeternum'" data-video-blog-id="9" data-video-network="kotaku" data-video-duration="108" data-playlist="197298,197284,197260" data-current="197298"><div><p>Live Forever in the Universe of 'New World: Aeternum'</p></div><video disablepictureinpicture="" muted="" playsinline="" width="100%" height="100%" crossorigin="anonymous" preload="none"><source data-src="https://vid.kinja.com/prod/197298/197298_240p.mp4" label="240p" type="video/mp4"><source data-src="https://vid.kinja.com/prod/197298/197298_480p.mp4" label="480p" type="video/mp4"><source data-src="https://vid.kinja.com/prod/197298/197298_720p.mp4" label="720p" type="video/mp4"><source data-src="https://vid.kinja.com/prod/197298/197298_1080p.mp4" label="1080p" type="video/mp4"></video></div><div><h4>Suggested Reading</h4></div><p>Since the heel turn that will live in infamy, the derided superstar has been leaving a trail of messages on X (formerly known as Twitter) leading us to the eventual unveiling of his new, evil personality. He’s educated his followers on discipline to make uncomfortable choices for the greater good, reduced any criticism of him to a reflection of the critics’ failings, and essentially told that in due time history will vindicate his decisions. Less than 12 hours before his first televised appearance since Elimination Chamber, Cena took to X to send one last cryptic message before the Evil Cena era begins:</p><figure id="" data-id="63809bde3d4c6869e1f7d0dd06d2cf68" data-recommend-id="image://63809bde3d4c6869e1f7d0dd06d2cf68" data-format="png" data-width="1007" data-height="395" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="John Cena's final tweet before public appearance" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="John Cena's final tweet before public appearance" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->X</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="63809bde3d4c6869e1f7d0dd06d2cf68" data-recommend-id="image://63809bde3d4c6869e1f7d0dd06d2cf68" data-format="png" data-width="1007" data-height="395" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="John Cena's final tweet before public appearance" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>The theme music was the same, but it was accompanied by a chorus of fans yelling “John Cena sucks” to the tune of “the time is now” before being flooded with a wave of boos. And the internet basked in it all.</p><figure id="" data-id="1bd706147e5a862fbd959400d5c53d36" data-recommend-id="image://1bd706147e5a862fbd959400d5c53d36" data-format="png" data-width="982" data-height="398" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="Fan responds to John Cena" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Fan responds to John Cena" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->X</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="1bd706147e5a862fbd959400d5c53d36" data-recommend-id="image://1bd706147e5a862fbd959400d5c53d36" data-format="png" data-width="982" data-height="398" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="Fan responds to John Cena" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>When it finally came time for Cena to answer for his sins and explain the most inexplicable heel turn ever, the 47-year-old wrestler attributed his switch to the 25 years of fans constantly asking for more from John Cena the wrestler regardless of John Cena the man felt. “For 25 years, I’ve been the victim of an abusive relationship,” Cena began explaining. “All you’ve ever done is bully me into being your damn puppet and expect me to do it with a smile on my face.” To him, he’s not babyface or a heel. He’s a human being. But, to wrestling fans, he’s unrecognizable. </p><figure id="" data-id="5745e99889bbecab177cbb542125f50f" data-recommend-id="image://5745e99889bbecab177cbb542125f50f" data-format="png" data-width="1001" data-height="376" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="Fan comparing John Cena to Homelander" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Fan comparing John Cena to Homelander" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->X</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="5745e99889bbecab177cbb542125f50f" data-recommend-id="image://5745e99889bbecab177cbb542125f50f" data-format="png" data-width="1001" data-height="376" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="Fan comparing John Cena to Homelander" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><figure id="" data-id="946a40c536ea4130422305fdf8259134" data-recommend-id="image://946a40c536ea4130422305fdf8259134" data-format="png" data-width="1002" data-height="360" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="Fan upset at John Cena" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Fan upset at John Cena" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->X</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="946a40c536ea4130422305fdf8259134" data-recommend-id="image://946a40c536ea4130422305fdf8259134" data-format="png" data-width="1002" data-height="360" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="Fan upset at John Cena" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><figure id="" data-id="145217dd8ecd67ae0938c54af2733f74" data-recommend-id="image://145217dd8ecd67ae0938c54af2733f74" data-format="png" data-width="991" data-height="334" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="John Cena compared to the Winter Soldier" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="John Cena compared to the Winter Soldier" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->X</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="145217dd8ecd67ae0938c54af2733f74" data-recommend-id="image://145217dd8ecd67ae0938c54af2733f74" data-format="png" data-width="991" data-height="334" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="John Cena compared to the Winter Soldier" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><figure id="" data-id="c2e79989b50346adc4c84df5be065662" data-recommend-id="image://c2e79989b50346adc4c84df5be065662" data-format="png" data-width="987" data-height="1414" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="John Cena being attacked online" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="John Cena being attacked online" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->X</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="c2e79989b50346adc4c84df5be065662" data-recommend-id="image://c2e79989b50346adc4c84df5be065662" data-format="png" data-width="987" data-height="1414" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="John Cena being attacked online" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>As is often the case, the fans’ Cena hate is just unrequited love, especially after the 16-time WWE Champion said he’s dissolving the 25-year relationship he’s had with the fans. You can’t erase decades of dedication in a few weeks or one promo. To say the least, people were delirious with mixed emotions, and one child realized his hero hated him.</p><figure id="" data-id="644aa1be76b6af75981fb26aa637439b" data-recommend-id="image://644aa1be76b6af75981fb26aa637439b" data-format="png" data-width="956" data-height="896" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="Kid crying at John Cena" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Kid crying at John Cena" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->X</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="644aa1be76b6af75981fb26aa637439b" data-recommend-id="image://644aa1be76b6af75981fb26aa637439b" data-format="png" data-width="956" data-height="896" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="Kid crying at John Cena" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><figure id="" data-id="a790931803f386519dc8f052d934696c" data-recommend-id="image://a790931803f386519dc8f052d934696c" data-format="png" data-width="977" data-height="874" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="X user responding to John Cena" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="X user responding to John Cena" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->X</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="a790931803f386519dc8f052d934696c" data-recommend-id="image://a790931803f386519dc8f052d934696c" data-format="png" data-width="977" data-height="874" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="X user responding to John Cena" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><figure id="" data-id="d6c305e057d4dffa58416298f2935afa" data-recommend-id="image://d6c305e057d4dffa58416298f2935afa" data-format="png" data-width="768" data-height="1462" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="X user responding to John Cena" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="X user responding to John Cena" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->X</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="d6c305e057d4dffa58416298f2935afa" data-recommend-id="image://d6c305e057d4dffa58416298f2935afa" data-format="png" data-width="768" data-height="1462" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="X user responding to John Cena" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><figure id="" data-id="5fe2e9176f0115158b41980add94d19d" data-recommend-id="image://5fe2e9176f0115158b41980add94d19d" data-format="png" data-width="1007" data-height="1462" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="Distraught fan" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Distraught fan" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->X</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="5fe2e9176f0115158b41980add94d19d" data-recommend-id="image://5fe2e9176f0115158b41980add94d19d" data-format="png" data-width="1007" data-height="1462" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="Distraught fan" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><figure id="" data-id="4d5efe9b5eb2ae16e86574104a581486" data-recommend-id="image://4d5efe9b5eb2ae16e86574104a581486" data-format="png" data-width="1007" data-height="857" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="X user reacting to John Cena" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="X user reacting to John Cena" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->X</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="4d5efe9b5eb2ae16e86574104a581486" data-recommend-id="image://4d5efe9b5eb2ae16e86574104a581486" data-format="png" data-width="1007" data-height="857" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="X user reacting to John Cena" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>If this is how Evil Cena’s era will start, we’re in for some generational hating, and possibly the birth of the most hated wrestler in WWE history. </p></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
